Service Cloud
Set Up Your Service Catalog Site

Use the Service Catalog site to open your Service Catalog to customers and partners. The site requires a CRM-powered self-service setup in Salesforce Setup and Experience Builder.

Before setting up, set up required permission assignments and build a Service Catalog with at least one active fulfillment, catalog category, and catalog item.

To get started:

1. Learn the Basics:
	* Review glossary, resource hub, and site basics overview
2. Get Ready to Build Your Site:
	* Familiarize yourself with CRM configurations and permissions assignments
3. Build, Customize, and Launch Your Site:
	* Use Experience Builder to build, customize, and launch your Aura or LWR Service Catalog site
4. Extend Your Site with AI (Beta):
	* Set up Einstein Copilot in Service Catalog to help customers resolve questions faster

Required Editions:

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions with the Customer Service Catalog add-on license.

The Service Catalog User permission set and a Channel Account, Customer Community, or Partner Community license are also required.
title: Setting Up Salesforce Service Catalog Site
